'''Maaban''' is a remote populated place in [[Ghana]]. Its coordinates are: Latitude (DMS): 6° 59′ 0″ N; Longitude (DMS): 2° 13′ 0″. [[tribesman|Tribesmen]] from Maaban were studied by Rosen in a seminal study<ref>S. Rosen and P. Olin, ''Hearing Loss and Coronary [[Heart Disease]]'', Archives of [[Otolaryngology]], 82:236 (1965)</ref> proving that hearing loss is primarily associated with exposure to [[noise pollution|elevated sound levels]], rather than a function of [[ageing]]. Rosen's work also showed that high sound levels were responsible for a statistical elevation of [[blood pressure]].
==See also== *[[Noise health effects]]
